The paper proposes a probabilistic algorithm for computing a basis of the Riemann-Roch space associated to a divisor on a projective plane curve over a field. This involves computations in algebraic geometry, number theory, and linear algebra. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The algorithm also has a geometric flavor, as it involves computations on a curve, so cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with probabilistic analysis of the algorithm, which falls under cs.SC (Symbolic Computation).
